parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
Spare tire failure can leave the driver stranded, causing inconvenience and potential safety risks.
Excessive tire wear and damage can lead to tire failure, causing loss of vehicle control and accidents.
symptoms: damage to wheel wells and vehicle components.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration and Cruise Control Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control system can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: the RPM gauge goes beyond normal range
the vehicle fails to decelerate when the brake pedal is depressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fire Hazard due to Electrical or Cruise Control Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system or cruise control can cause a fire, leading to vehicle damage, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke appears from the brake pedal
oil dripping from a defective master cylinder
fire starts in the engine area.

consumers are told to wait for an extended period
